Nearest Centroid Classifier¶

In [664]:
def getPrototypeVectors(records, labels):
    classesDict = {}
    countDict = {}
    for i in labels.unique():
        classesDict[i] = np.zeros(records.shape[1])
        countDict[i] = 0
    for i in range(len(records)):
        currClass = labels.iloc[i]
        countDict[currClass] += 1
        classesDict[currClass] = classesDict[currClass] + records.iloc[i]
    for key,value in countDict.iteritems():
        classesDict[key] = classesDict[key] / value
    return classesDict
In [665]:
#define a function to calculate the distance between two vectors using 
#cosine similarity
def calcCosineSimilarity(x1, x2):
    x1Norm = np.linalg.norm(x1)
    x2Norm = np.linalg.norm(x2)
    sims = np.dot(x1,x2) / (x1Norm * x2Norm)
    return sims
In [666]:
def testNearestCentroid(test_set, classesDict):
    classifications = []
    for i in range(len(test_set)):
        currTest = test_set.iloc[i]
        maxSimilarity = -2
        classPredicion = ''
        for key, value in classesDict.iteritems():
            cosSimilarity = calcCosineSimilarity(value, currTest)
            if (cosSimilarity > maxSimilarity):
                maxSimilarity = cosSimilarity
                classPrediction = key
        classifications.append(classPrediction)
    return classifications
In [667]:
def calculateNearestCentroidCorrectness(classifications, real_labels):
    correctNumber = 0
    totalNumber = 0
    for i in range(len(classifications)):
        print ("predict: " + classifications[i])
        print ("real: " + real_labels.iloc[i])
        if classifications[i] == real_labels.iloc[i]:
            correctNumber += 1
        totalNumber += 1
    percentCorrect = float(correctNumber) / totalNumber
    return percentCorrect

In [377]:

In [381]:
#normalize the data
min_max_scaler = preprocessing.MinMaxScaler().fit(X_train)
train_norm = min_max_scaler.transform(X_train)
test_norm = min_max_scaler.transform(X_test)
In [620]:
def knnTester(xTrain, yTrain, xTest, yTest):
    results = pd.DataFrame()
    for n_neighbors in range(1, 25):
        distance_knnclf = neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors, weights="distance")
        distance_knnclf.fit(xTrain, yTrain)
        distance_score = distance_knnclf.score(xTest, yTest)
        uniform_knnclf = neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors, weights="uniform")
        uniform_knnclf.fit(xTrain, yTrain)
        uniform_score = uniform_knnclf.score(xTest, yTest)
        results = results.append([[n_neighbors, distance_score, uniform_score]])
    results.columns = ["Neighbors", "DistanceScore", "UniformScore"]
    return results
In [621]:
res = knnTester(train_norm, Y_train, test_norm, Y_test)
